<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>right now the exception message shown is "Bad log priority".</p>

<p>But that may not be the actual reason for the error. Suppose in my code I have</p>

<p>$log-&gt;addEventItem('foo','bar');</p>

<p>This would throw the "Bad log priority" exception message since __call() is overridden to provide a convenience method for doing
$log-&gt;priorityName('message');
instead of
$log-&gt;log('message', Zend_Log::PRIORITY_NAME);</p>

<p>the current exception message thrown isn't helpful because it is context sensitive. A more useful message would be "__call() is unable to trap the method $method" or something to that effect.</p>

